article.headline: Florida A&M 67, Bethune Cookman 65
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- Tony Tate's three-point play with 17 seconds left gave Florida A&M a 67-65 victory over Bethune-Cookman Thursday night in the regular season finale for both teams. The Rattlers (13-14, 10-8 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) won for the sixth time in their last seven games and moved into the seventh seed for next week's conference tournament in Richmond, Va. Bethune-Cookman (12-16, 8-10) lost its fourth straight. The Wildcats trailed 60-50 with 5:37 to play, but rallied to take the lead at 65-64 on Antonio Webb's 3-pointer with 32 seconds left. Tate drove the lane for a lay-up to put the Rattlers ahead. Tate was fouled and hit a free throw to score the final point. Darius Glover blocked a shot by Michael Williams II to preserve the victory for the Rattlers, who managed to split the regular season series with their rival. Glover led the Rattlers with 19 points, followed by James Pattman with 13 and O.J. Sumter, who had 11 points and a game-high 13 rebounds. Bethune-Cookman had five players in double figures, led by Williams with 13 and Webb, Diondre Larmond, Kory Crumbly and Cleveland Williams each with 11.
